TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Goal Programming Approach to Aggregate Planning of Production and Work Force
AU  - Goodman, David A.
Y1  - 1974/08/01
PY  - 1974
DA  - 1974/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.20.12.1569
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.20.12.1569
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1569
EP  - 1575
VL  - 20
IS  - 12
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper presents a goal programming approach to the problem of scheduling aggregate production and work force. The approach is illustrated via two case applications. Numeric results are derived and compared to those of two other approaches. The results suggest that goal programming may be an effective approach for solving certain types of planning models.
AB  - This paper presents a goal programming approach to the problem of scheduling aggregate production and work force. The approach is illustrated via two case applications. Numeric results are derived and compared to those of two other approaches. The results suggest that goal programming may be an effective approach for solving certain types of planning models.
